title: Compiling (via emerge) nightly rust 1.66.1 fails on Gentoo - unexpected panic in compiler

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
I am trying to install Rust on my Gentoo machine. I was able to install the stable version (`1.65`) but when I enable nightly features and try to upgrade to `1.66.1`, I get the errors pasted below. The backtrace indicates that this is rustc compile issue (and not Gentoo-specific presumably), hence I am opening an issue here.

`rustc --version --verbose`:
```

commit-hash: unknown

host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu
release: 1.65.0
LLVM version: 15.0.0
```
